Futaba Corporation Logo Futaba Corporation is a Japanese company founded in 1948, originally to produce vacuum tubes. As time passed, production and elemental techniques of the vacuum tube transformed into the manufacturing of vacuum fluorescent displays, tool and die set components, radio control equipment and OLED displays.
